<h2>Focal Planes</h2>

<p> The Department has supplied the focal planes used on <a
href="../research/dataanalysis.html">CIRS</a> and PMIRR. The
images below are of the focal plane used on CIRS, which is set to
reach its destination Saturn in 2004.

<p> <center> <table> <tr> <td><center> <img src="FPA_cover2.jpg"><br>
<i>Focal Plane Cover</i> </center></td>

<td><center> <img src="FPA_plan2.jpg"><br> <i>Focal Plane Plan</i>
</center></td> </tr> </table> </center>

<center> <img src="FPA2.jpg"><br> <i>Focal Plane</i> </center>

<p>The optics are bought from Reading University. Here, we package and
align the detectors and optics. The focal planes are aligned within
one of our <a href="../facilities/clean_areas.html">clean areas</a> in the <a
href="../facilities/space_view_chamber.html">Space View Chamber</a>. The alignment
is performed in a complete vacuum. Then by scanning a chop pin-hole
source in front of the focal plane we can locate the first image of
the detectors.

<center><img src="ATR_xyz2.jpg"><br> <i>The image above is of the
vacuum compatable 3 axis image positioner used to do the
scanning.</i></center>


